## 5. Review Questions

### Q1: Difference Between Bit Rate and Baud Rate

- **Bit Rate**: Number of bits transmitted per second.
- **Baud Rate**: Number of signal units transmitted per second.
- **Relationship**: Baud Rate ≤ Bit Rate (due to encoding).

### Q2: Different Types of Modes of Communication

- **Simplex**
- **Half-Duplex**
- **Full-Duplex**

### Q3: Difference Between Full Duplex, Half Duplex, and Simplex

| Mode       | Transmission Direction | Simultaneity |
|------------|------------------------|--------------|
| Simplex    | One-way                 | No           |
| Half-Duplex | Two-way                 | Alternating  |
| Full-Duplex | Two-way                 | Simultaneous |

### Q4: Standards of Organization

- **De Jure Standards**: Officially recognized standards developed through formal processes.
- **De Facto Standards**: Widely accepted practices or products without official recognition.

### Q5: Understanding Signals

- **Types of Signals**:
  - Analog: Continuous waveforms
  - Digital: Discrete values

### Q6: Causes of Impairment

- **Attenuation**: Loss of strength over distance
- **Distortion**: Changes in waveform shape
- **Noise**: External interference

### Q7: Periodic vs Non-Periodic Signals

- **Periodic Signals**: Repeat at regular intervals
- **Non-Periodic Signals**: Irregular or random waveforms

### Q8: Definitions

| Term       | Definition                                                                 |
|------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Bit Rate   | Number of bits per second                                                 |
| Baud Rate  | Number of signal units per second                                         |
| Bit Length | Physical distance covered by one bit on the transmission medium          |
| Bit Interval | Time interval between consecutive bits                                  |

### Q9: Understand Defacto and DeJure

- **De Jure**: Formally established standards.
- **De Facto**: Accepted norms or products, often from leading companies.

### Q10: Understand Protocol

- **Protocol**: Set of rules governing communication between entities.
- **Protocol Architecture**: Hierarchical structure defining layers of communication.

